translated: Johnsson, Gustaf Wilhelm, executive, Ronneby, born on February 23rd, 1892 in Stockholm to real estate owners Jonas J. and Anna Zetter-ström. Married in 19xx to Helga Fredriksson. Completed studies at Stockholm's technical institute and commercial school. Traveled to Germany, Czechoslovakia, Austria, and France. Employed at A-B Läderfabr. Welting in Stockholm from 1913-1918, and has been a manager at A-B Läderfabr. Welting in Ronneby since 1918. He is a board member of the aforementioned company and a substitute board member for the Swedish tanning industry association and several other industry associations. He is also a member of the city council, executive committee, port authority, and commerce and shipping council in Ronneby, and a substitute member of the social welfare committee. His hobby is fishing, and he has received the Patriotic Society Medal.
